data.content:
## What breaks: Cosmos DB sync I/O is fully removed in EF Core 11

In .NET 10, you could opt into sync-over-async for the Cosmos provider. **In EF Core 11, that opt-in is gone.** All synchronous I/O APIs (`ToList()`, `First()`, `Count()`, `SaveChanges()`, etc.) now **always throw** â€” no configuration can restore them.

### Fix: convert to async

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

**Key points:**
- `ToList()` â†’ `await ToListAsync()`
- `First()` â†’ `await FirstAsync()`
- `Count()` â†’ `await CountAsync()`
- `SaveChanges()` â†’ `await SaveChangesAsync()`
- All callers up the chain must also become `async`/`await`

This is the only path forward â€” the Cosmos SDK is async-only, and EF Core 11 no longer wraps it synchronously. Tracking issue: [dotnet/efcore#37059](https://github.com/dotnet/efcore/issues/37059).
